translated: Hagberg, Axel Yngve, physician, dentist, Gothenburg, b. March 10th, 1900 in Sandseryd, Jönköping County, son of vicar Emil H. and Agnes Bergh. Married in 1928 to Gunborg Margareta Dahlqvist, with whom he had three children: Gunnar, born in 1929, Georg, born in 1932, and Marianne, born in 1935. Hagberg obtained his high school diploma in Jönköping in 1920, followed by a medical degree from Uppsala University in 1923, and a medical license in 1928. He also became a licensed dentist in 1931. He worked as an assistant physician at the Southern Vi Health Spa in 1927, as well as assistant physician in the surgical department at Uppsala University Hospital in 1928-1929, and at the surgical department in Linköping and Sahlgr. hospital in 1928. He served as a temporary medical examiner in Vin-delns and Kisa districts, and as a railway physician in Rätansbyn district in 1928, and in the Malå-Träsk, Vännäs, and Umeå districts in 1929, as well as a temporary city and hospital physician in Askersund in 1929. From 1931-1936, he worked as a general practitioner and dentist in Nossebro, and from 1936, he worked as a specialized physician on oral and dental diseases in Gothenburg. His hobby was hunting.
